				 Border clashes
 Islamabad, Oct. 7 (AP):  Islamic militants and Pakistani troops fought two major  battles near the Afghan border today, killing 50 guerrillas  and 20 troops, the army said.																								Both clashes occurred in North Waziristan, a stronghold of pro-Taliban militants near the Afghan border, army spokesperson Major General Waheed Arshad said.																								Security forces launched an operation against the militants after they attacked troops overnight, Arshad said.
